Bluetongue, Bulgaria
--------------------
Information received on [and dated] 7 Aug 2014 from Prof Nikola T Belev, OIE Delegate, OIE Regional Representation for Eastern Europe, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, Sofia, Bulgaria

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no 1
Date of start of the event: 4 Jul 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 11 Jul 2014
Report date: 7 Aug 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 7 Aug 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 27 Mar 2008
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to the whole country

[For detailed statistics and other information pertaining to each of the 140 new outbreaks, including an interactive map, please refer to the full report at the source URL above. The disease is concentrated mainly in south Bulgaria, bordering Greece and Turkey. - Mod.AS]

