Bluetongue, Greece
------------------
Information received on [and dated] 6 Aug 2014 from Spiros Doudounakis, Director, Animal Health Directorate, Directorate General of Veterinary Services/Animal Health Directorate, Ministry of Rural Development and Food, Athens, Greece

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no 6
Date of start of the event: 29 May 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 30 May 2014
Report date: 6 Aug 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 6 Aug 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 13 Aug 2013
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

[For detailed statistics and other information pertaining to each of the 66 new outbreaks, including an interactive map, please refer to the full report at the source URL above. The disease is not restricted any more to the Peloponnese region, where it continued its spread, but has now penetrated into the northern regions of Greece, including the provinces of East Macedonia and Thrace, Central Greece, West Macedonia, and Central Macedonia. - Mod.AS]

