Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[BTV serotype 4 seems to have widely spread throughout Greece and southern Bulgaria, affecting almost exclusively sheep. This is not surprising: since sheep are known as the clinically affected species concerning most BTV serotypes. Infection in cattle and goats is common but known to remain subclinical (serotype 8 is an exception).

In the absence of vaccination, losses in sheep may be heavy, particularly in breeds known to be more susceptible. - Mod.AS]

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2668336,83. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

