[3] Italy: serotype 1, spread
Date: Wed 6 Aug 2014
Source: The Cattle Site [edited]
http://www.thecattlesite.com/news/46283/bluetongue-still-rising-in-italy


Bluetongue still rising in Italy
--------------------------------
A spate of bluetongue outbreaks has been reported across southern and central Italy in cattle and sheep.

According to the World Organisation for Animal Health [OIE], the 17 outbreaks hit sheep the hardest, killing 54 animals from 54 cases.

Two cases were confirmed in cattle, leaving 117 animals susceptible.

The report, dated 5 Aug 2014, is the latest update since 5 outbreaks were reported in similar locations in mid-July [2014].

The biggest farm to be infected was in Anagni, near Frosinone in the Lazio region, with 6 cases and 789 animals classed as susceptible following confirmation from the Teramo National Laboratory.

The worst hit regions were Calabria in the south west, Campina, and Lazio.

The outbreaks are the latest in ongoing surveillance efforts following confirmation of the disease in sheep in September last year [2013].

