[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2668336,75. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

[For the details of the 17 new outbreaks covered in Italy's follow-up report no 16 of 5 Aug 2014, please see http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=15776. The report includes an interactive map.

This epizootic is caused by BTV serotype 1.

To view all BTV outbreaks in south Europe reported during 2014, please see OIE's global BTV map at http://tinyurl.com/o9hon45 (click on the cluster, zoom in). The observed apparent absence of outbreaks in Turkey is misleading; most likely, BTV-4 is currently circulating in this country as well. - Mod.AS]
